<span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"> PAGEREF _Toc760425614 \h </span>
  <span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"><span style="mso-element:field-separator"></span></span><span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB">1</span>
  <span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"></span><span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"><span style="mso-element:field-end"></span></span></a></span></span></p>

<p class="MsoToc1"><span class="MsoHyperlink"><span lang="EN-GB" style="mso-no-proof:yes" xml:lang="EN-GB">
<a href="#_Toc916223300">Bibliography<span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB">
<span style="mso-tab-count:1 dotted">. </span></span><span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB">
<span style="mso-element:field-begin"></span></span>
<span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"> PAGEREF _Toc916223300 \h </span>
  <span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"><span style="mso-element:field-separator"></span></span><span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB">1</span>
  <span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"></span><span lang="EN-GB" class="MsoTocTextSpan" xml:lang="EN-GB"><span style="mso-element:field-end"></span></span></a></span></span></p>

<p class="MsoToc1"><span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"><span style="mso-element:field-end"></span></span><span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"><o:p class="MsoNormal">&#xA0;</o:p></span></p>
</div><p class="MsoNormal"><br clear="all" style="mso-special-character:line-break;page-break-before:always"/></p><div><a name="_9684a353-1257-5326-1b54-4356a07b76a2" id="_9684a353-1257-5326-1b54-4356a07b76a2"></a><h1 class="AbstractTitle">I.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Abstract</h1><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_b9ca0b52-6d04-a80f-028c-00175f1f17d2" id="_b9ca0b52-6d04-a80f-028c-00175f1f17d2"></a>This OGC Standard defines EmissionML, a conceptual data model for representing emission events. EmissionML provides a domain-specific ontology for describing the release of substances into the atmosphere, including the source from which an emission originates, the mechanism by which it occurs, the quantity of substance released, and the temporal bounds of the event.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_97227bf7-e48d-f545-9ed6-d44b9cb0983d" id="_97227bf7-e48d-f545-9ed6-d44b9cb0983d"></a>EmissionML distinguishes itself through three key design principles. First, it incorporates an evidence chain linking emission determinations to supporting Observations, enabling traceability from reported values to underlying measurements. Second, it provides explicit uncertainty provenance by attaching data quality metadata to both emission quantities and temporal bounds, ensuring that the confidence and precision of each determination are recorded alongside the values themselves. Third, it offers clear spatial and temporal context &#x2014; spatial through Feature (as the ultimate feature of interest) and Source (as the emission origin), temporal through start time, end time, and the phenomenon time of supporting Observations. By adopting the OMS 3.0 Observation model, EmissionML provides a common framework for reconciling heterogeneous sensor observations &#x2014; from remote sensing satellites to ground-based continuous monitoring stations &#x2014; within a single, unified evidence chain.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_41b25f7b-745d-a208-2bfe-a3d8eaac71f1" id="_41b25f7b-745d-a208-2bfe-a3d8eaac71f1"></a>The model builds on foundational OGC and ISO standards. Source inherits from Feature (ISO 19109), DeterminationProcedure inherits from Procedure (ISO/OGC 19156:2023), and Observations conform to the OMS 3.0 Observation model (ISO/OGC 19156:2023). The standard defines twelve requirements specifying the structure and constraints of the core data model.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_a404ec89-1cb6-dc08-5a17-eb9965c8ca94" id="_a404ec89-1cb6-dc08-5a17-eb9965c8ca94"></a>By making emission semantics, evidence chains, and uncertainty provenance explicit and machine-verifiable, EmissionML enables credibility of reported emission values, traceability from determinations to their supporting observations and procedures, and reproducibility of emission assessments across organizations and jurisdictions.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_74098f89-342b-2430-35ab-3560e174e9cf" id="_74098f89-342b-2430-35ab-3560e174e9cf"></a>The intended audience includes environmental regulators, greenhouse gas reporting frameworks, emissions monitoring system developers, and geospatial data infrastructure implementers who require a standardized, interoperable representation of emission event data.</p></div><div class="Section3"><a name="_a1ef2e03-18b5-a689-0607-918dc7819660" id="_a1ef2e03-18b5-a689-0607-918dc7819660"></a><h1 class="IntroTitle">II.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Keywords</h1><p class="MsoNormal">The following are keywords to be used by search engines and document catalogues.</p><p class="MsoNormal">ogcdoc, OGC document, EmissionML, emission event, atmospheric emissions, greenhouse gas, air quality, emission source, emission quantity, observation, data quality, uncertainty provenance, evidence chain, interoperability, net-zero, methane emissions, sensor web</p></div><p class="MsoNormal"><br clear="all" style="mso-special-character:line-break;page-break-before:always"/></p><div><a name="_522557ea-b3d2-a6ac-c804-2ee9c762e696" id="_522557ea-b3d2-a6ac-c804-2ee9c762e696"></a><h1 class="ForewordTitle">III.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Preface</h1><div class="Note"><a name="_c6da8652-bca4-650d-53ae-a7a949f07518" id="_c6da8652-bca4-650d-53ae-a7a949f07518"></a><p class="Note"><span class="note_label">NOTE:<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span></span>Insert Preface Text here. Give OGC specific commentary: describe the technical content, reason for document, history of the document and precursors, and plans for future work. &gt; Attention is drawn to the possibility that some of the elements of this document may be the subject of patent rights. The Open Geospatial Consortium shall not be held responsible for identifying any or all such patent rights.</p><p class="Note"><a name="_ec96a99d-f434-0909-a192-b36dd45d6cb8" id="_ec96a99d-f434-0909-a192-b36dd45d6cb8"></a>Recipients of this document are requested to submit, with their comments, notification of any relevant patent claims or other intellectual property rights of which they may be aware that might be infringed by any implementation of the standard set forth in this document, and to provide supporting documentation.</p></div></div><div class="Section3"><a name="_b99a2bd6-1a97-8f41-0bc0-600ae6df3c97" id="_b99a2bd6-1a97-8f41-0bc0-600ae6df3c97"></a><h1 class="IntroTitle">IV.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Security Considerations</h1><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_b2512eeb-995a-eabe-4ee2-ae30853fc76e" id="_b2512eeb-995a-eabe-4ee2-ae30853fc76e"></a>No security considerations have been made for this Standard.</p></div><div class="Section3"><a name="_40a5ccef-53b2-af45-4e4b-1f6aef9e07d3" id="_40a5ccef-53b2-af45-4e4b-1f6aef9e07d3"></a><h1 class="IntroTitle">V.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Submitting Organizations</h1><p class="MsoNormal">The following organizations submitted this Document to the Open Geospatial Consortium (OGC):</p><div class="ul_wrap"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo1;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_b4e36d79-9313-a8e0-7b17-a69836220a87" id="_b4e36d79-9313-a8e0-7b17-a69836220a87"></a>SensorUp Inc.</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo1;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_892cc9e6-a378-ae5f-c151-bd31cd4c4bc7" id="_892cc9e6-a378-ae5f-c151-bd31cd4c4bc7"></a>Natural Resources Canada</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo1;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast"><a name="_e3464e0d-41c7-1fb8-d305-1da52a02e67f" id="_e3464e0d-41c7-1fb8-d305-1da52a02e67f"></a>University of Calgary</p></div></div><div class="Section3"><a name="_b9b7521c-b2e3-7764-d410-ae4494400cf2" id="_b9b7521c-b2e3-7764-d410-ae4494400cf2"></a><h1 class="IntroTitle">VI.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Submitters</h1><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_6e1b734b-e32c-864b-59a1-81792b76695c" id="_6e1b734b-e32c-864b-59a1-81792b76695c"></a>All questions regarding this submission should be directed to the editor or the submitters:</p><p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table&#xA0;&#x2014; Submitters</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;"><a name="_271dcaec-fbfa-1848-5c62-cb94dc01b25f" id="_271dcaec-fbfa-1848-5c62-cb94dc01b25f"></a><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><b>Name</b></td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><b>Affiliation</b></td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Steve Liang</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">University of Calgary / SensorUp</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">Ryan Ahola</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">Natural Resources Canada</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><p class="MsoNormal">&#xA0;</p></div>
    <p class="MsoNormal">
      <br clear="all" class="section"/>
    </p>
    <div class="WordSection3">
      <div>
        <a name="_b8120984-2cf7-386d-e9f0-aba3393c2bd8" id="_b8120984-2cf7-386d-e9f0-aba3393c2bd8"></a>
        <h1>1.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Scope</h1>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_b513b7c3-b586-c180-d051-a50bc75a1307" id="_b513b7c3-b586-c180-d051-a50bc75a1307"></a>This document defines a conceptual data model for emission events, for features from which emissions originate and mechanisms by which they occur, and for observations and procedures that provide evidence for emission determinations. These provide models for the exchange of information describing emission events and their associated quantities, temporal bounds, sources, and mechanisms, both within and between different regulatory, scientific, and technical communities.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_39bde1b8-116d-e2f4-7921-3073b6718fb7" id="_39bde1b8-116d-e2f4-7921-3073b6718fb7"></a>Emission events commonly involve observations of an ultimate feature-of-interest at varying spatial scales. This document defines a common set of classes for describing emission sources, mechanisms, quantities, temporal bounds, determination procedures, and supporting observations. The schema includes relationships between emission events and their evidence chains, linking reported values to underlying observations and procedures, and attaches data quality metadata to emission quantities and temporal bounds.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_3761b7b5-cce0-6300-9e08-6ceb80808c18" id="_3761b7b5-cce0-6300-9e08-6ceb80808c18"></a>This document concerns only externally visible interfaces and places no restriction on the underlying implementations other than what is needed to satisfy the interface specifications in the actual situation.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <a name="_fb6900df-d347-21c7-37e0-9bed416628c1" id="_fb6900df-d347-21c7-37e0-9bed416628c1"></a>
        <h1>2.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Conformance</h1>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_6edb708c-b3ff-cefb-f9ef-a2a80050a4e1" id="_6edb708c-b3ff-cefb-f9ef-a2a80050a4e1"></a>This Standard defines a conceptual data model for emission events.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_b0c51a56-4db6-c0cb-eaa4-3935c35ffd6e" id="_b0c51a56-4db6-c0cb-eaa4-3935c35ffd6e"></a>Requirements for one standardization target type are considered:</p>
        <div class="ul_wrap"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_7a1c2347-e4d7-2379-e699-fbc818f000d4" id="_7a1c2347-e4d7-2379-e699-fbc818f000d4"></a>Data Model
</p>
</div>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_99182ca0-9d6d-c327-69a2-017bc6cbffc4" id="_99182ca0-9d6d-c327-69a2-017bc6cbffc4"></a>Conformance with this Standard shall be checked using all the relevant tests specified in Annex A (normative) of this document. The framework, concepts, and methodology for testing, and the criteria to be achieved to claim conformance are specified in the OGC Compliance Testing Policies and Procedures and the OGC Compliance Testing web site.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_43e264e0-d11d-b3aa-8156-2b432aef4de7" id="_43e264e0-d11d-b3aa-8156-2b432aef4de7"></a>In order to conform to this OGC&#xAE; Standard, a software implementation shall choose to implement:</p>
        <div class="ul_wrap"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo3;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_0f672998-ae16-ff76-a597-ba223334da90" id="_0f672998-ae16-ff76-a597-ba223334da90"></a>The Emission Event Conceptual Data Model Core conformance class specified in Annex A (normative).
</p>
</div>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_b8c6ed5c-4454-487f-05a7-4f7c6222ae23" id="_b8c6ed5c-4454-487f-05a7-4f7c6222ae23"></a>All requirements-classes and conformance-classes described in this document are owned by the Standard(s) identified.</p>
      </div>
      <div><h1>3.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Normative references</h1>
<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_49996d2b-65c1-916b-9bbf-42b933aa0025" id="_49996d2b-65c1-916b-9bbf-42b933aa0025"></a>The following documents are referred to in the text in such a way that some or all of their content constitutes requirements of this document. For dated references, only the edition cited applies. For undated references, the latest edition of the referenced document (including any amendments) applies.</p>



<p class="NormRef"><a name="ISO19101-1" id="ISO19101-1"></a>ISO: ISO&#xA0;19101-1:2014, <i>Geographic information&#x2009;&#x2014;&#x2009;Reference model&#x2009;&#x2014;&#x2009;Part 1: Fundamentals</i>. International Organization for Standardization, Geneva (2014). <a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/59164.html">https://www.iso.org/standard/59164.html</a>.</p>
<p class="NormRef"><a name="ISO19107" id="ISO19107"></a>ISO: ISO&#xA0;19107:2019, <i>Geographic information&#x2009;&#x2014;&#x2009;Spatial schema</i>. International Organization for Standardization, Geneva (2019). <a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/66175.html">https://www.iso.org/standard/66175.html</a>.</p>
<p class="NormRef"><a name="ISO19108" id="ISO19108"></a>ISO: ISO&#xA0;19108:2002, <i>Geographic information&#x2009;&#x2014;&#x2009;Temporal schema</i>. International Organization for Standardization, Geneva (2002). <a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/26013.html">https://www.iso.org/standard/26013.html</a>.</p>
<p class="NormRef"><a name="ISO19109" id="ISO19109"></a>ISO: ISO&#xA0;19109:2015, <i>Geographic information&#x2009;&#x2014;&#x2009;Rules for application schema</i>. International Organization for Standardization, Geneva (2015). <a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/59193.html">https://www.iso.org/standard/59193.html</a>.</p>
<p class="NormRef"><a name="ISO19157" id="ISO19157"></a>ISO: ISO&#xA0;19157:2013, <i>Geographic information &#x2009;&#x2014;&#x2009;Data quality</i>. International Organization for Standardization, Geneva (2013). <a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/32575.html">https://www.iso.org/standard/32575.html</a>.</p>
<p class="NormRef"><a name="ISO19156" id="ISO19156"></a>ISO: ISO&#xA0;19156:2023, <i>Geographic information&#x2009;&#x2014;&#x2009;Observations, measurements and samples</i>. International Organization for Standardization, Geneva (2023). <a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/82463.html">https://www.iso.org/standard/82463.html</a>.</p>
</div>
      <div><a name="_89816945-de22-3a32-4531-afd4ccd4be30" id="_89816945-de22-3a32-4531-afd4ccd4be30"></a><h1>4.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Terms and definitions</h1>
<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_9608c37a-eaae-1098-3a4b-f705fd512d85" id="_9608c37a-eaae-1098-3a4b-f705fd512d85"></a>No terms and definitions are listed in this document.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_6e5ba0bf-4830-2e53-f1c5-07c075342c8f" id="_6e5ba0bf-4830-2e53-f1c5-07c075342c8f"></a>This document uses the terms defined in <a href="https://portal.ogc.org/public_ogc/directives/directives.php">OGC Policy Directive 49</a>, which is based on the ISO/IEC Directives, Part 2, Rules for the structure and drafting of International Standards. In particular, the word &#x201C;shall&#x201D; (not &#x201C;must&#x201D;) is the verb form used to indicate a requirement to be strictly followed to conform to this Standard and OGC documents do not use the equivalent phrases in the ISO/IEC Directives, Part 2.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_2bcce6ff-440a-67d4-c0a7-a81fa5b1125e" id="_2bcce6ff-440a-67d4-c0a7-a81fa5b1125e"></a>This document also uses terms defined in the OGC Standard for Modular specifications (<a href="https://portal.opengeospatial.org/files/?artifact_id=34762">OGC 08-131r3</a>), also known as the &#x2018;ModSpec&#x2019;. The definitions of terms such as standard, specification, requirement, and conformance test are provided in the ModSpec.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_3a4cc38f-6614-34f0-6e5b-8831934c33d4" id="_3a4cc38f-6614-34f0-6e5b-8831934c33d4"></a>For the purposes of this document, the following additional terms and definitions apply.</p>

<table class="dl"><a name="_3ac1ea54-808f-7790-f660-2a0c3f64de0a" id="_3ac1ea54-808f-7790-f660-2a0c3f64de0a"></a><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Determination Procedure</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_3b3bd09f-e4b6-9cc0-3c43-2bb6be63f139" id="_3b3bd09f-e4b6-9cc0-3c43-2bb6be63f139"></a>A Determination Procedure describes the steps performed to determine the quantity or temporal bounds of an Emission Event.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Emission Event</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_145f0d93-c12f-2b74-9dc4-e8cab24a88cc" id="_145f0d93-c12f-2b74-9dc4-e8cab24a88cc"></a>An Emission Event represents the release of a substance into the atmosphere over a non-zero duration. It is characterized by its start time and end time, the Source Feature from which the substance originated, and the identity and quantity of the emitted substance.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Emission Quantity</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_f2792530-c7a8-85a6-fdeb-8f3d3e4f3895" id="_f2792530-c7a8-85a6-fdeb-8f3d3e4f3895"></a>An Emission Quantity is the physical quantity representing the total mass of substance released to the atmosphere during a defined Emission Event or over a specified time interval.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Emission Intent</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_34b85bee-0de0-6abc-4ea2-64b70abb1a5f" id="_34b85bee-0de0-6abc-4ea2-64b70abb1a5f"></a>Emission Intent is a code list describing whether an emission is intentional, unintentional, or unknown.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Feature</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_508ce536-d3c4-1e5f-e5f2-7d568fe9843c" id="_508ce536-d3c4-1e5f-e5f2-7d568fe9843c"></a>Abstraction of real world phenomena (Source: ISO 19101-1:2014)</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Measurement</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_b793214b-1fed-e01e-9ff3-058348fb03ca" id="_b793214b-1fed-e01e-9ff3-058348fb03ca"></a>Set of operations having the object of determining the value of a quantity (Source: <a href="https://docs.ogc.org/as/20-082r4/20-082r4.html">ISO/OGC 19156:2023</a>)</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Mechanism</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_6f355a09-9773-1d39-87ff-b64abf51d395" id="_6f355a09-9773-1d39-87ff-b64abf51d395"></a>A Mechanism is a classification of the specific physical, chemical, or operational process that constitutes the direct cause or pathway for an emission. It is defined independently of the Source&#x2014;including its identity, structure, or purpose&#x2014;allowing Mechanisms to be consistently reused across different types of Source.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Observation</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_bc50a8a1-e6fb-4a60-5f64-9f5b543d90e0" id="_bc50a8a1-e6fb-4a60-5f64-9f5b543d90e0"></a>Act carried out by an observer to determine the value of an observable property of an object (feature-of-interest) by using a procedure, with the value provided as the result (Source: <a href="https://docs.ogc.org/as/20-082r4/20-082r4.html">ISO/OGC 19156:2023</a>)</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Procedure</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_107031e7-a437-afe5-c555-cbfb89f9789b" id="_107031e7-a437-afe5-c555-cbfb89f9789b"></a>Description of steps performed (Source: <a href="https://docs.ogc.org/as/20-082r4/20-082r4.html">ISO/OGC 19156:2023</a>)</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Source</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_45aa269b-d112-d03f-7629-6f2ba55768a2" id="_45aa269b-d112-d03f-7629-6f2ba55768a2"></a>A Source represents the feature from which an emission originates. A Source is an ISO 191xx feature whose geometry provides the geospatial reference for one or more Emission Events. A Source is characterised by its own identity, geometry, intended function, and lifecycle, and is explicitly agnostic to the Mechanism by which any associated Emission Event occurs.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Source Type</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_e1b4dbe9-1d30-8423-36c9-0e94ab85948a" id="_e1b4dbe9-1d30-8423-36c9-0e94ab85948a"></a>A Source Type classifies a Source by its category.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Temporal Bound</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_31913e52-3df5-2047-a1ab-023da3120d08" id="_31913e52-3df5-2047-a1ab-023da3120d08"></a>A Temporal Bound is a value object representing a temporal determination (e.g., start time or end time) that MAY have associated data quality metadata.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="left"><p align="left" style="margin-left:0pt;text-align:left;" class="MsoNormal">Unit of Measure</p></td><td valign="top"><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_d22b3e19-5db0-299a-d066-a35ed9982f30" id="_d22b3e19-5db0-299a-d066-a35ed9982f30"></a>Reference quantity chosen from a unit equivalence group (Source: <a href="https://docs.ogc.org/as/20-082r4/20-082r4.html">ISO/OGC 19156:2023</a>)</p>
</td></tr></table>
</div>
      <div>
        <a name="_33c4deb5-f5d4-f2bc-bb0b-f3c96e441003" id="_33c4deb5-f5d4-f2bc-bb0b-f3c96e441003"></a>
        <h1>5.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Keywords</h1>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_0816ce5d-64dc-31d2-2725-235fdb5a2913" id="_0816ce5d-64dc-31d2-2725-235fdb5a2913"></a>The following are keywords to be used by search engines and document catalogues.</p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_8ffdb2db-05bb-32ca-e4e5-b294ef23b525" id="_8ffdb2db-05bb-32ca-e4e5-b294ef23b525"></a>ogcdoc, OGC document, EmissionML, emission event, atmospheric emissions, greenhouse gas, air quality, emission source, emission quantity, observation, data quality, uncertainty provenance, evidence chain, interoperability, net-zero, methane emissions, sensor web</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <a name="_d02b5c44-c799-bfa6-3358-d1f5f0a4f020" id="_d02b5c44-c799-bfa6-3358-d1f5f0a4f020"></a>
        <h1>6.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Submitting organizations</h1>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_fd8bbdfb-3e79-72b0-40e5-51f0e567eae0" id="_fd8bbdfb-3e79-72b0-40e5-51f0e567eae0"></a>The following organizations submitted this Document to the Open Geospatial Consortium (OGC):</p>
        <div class="ul_wrap"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo4;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_af96efe9-f759-25b5-9aa9-bf5d14bcd43a" id="_af96efe9-f759-25b5-9aa9-bf5d14bcd43a"></a>SensorUp Inc.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo4;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_a9ca2a6f-dc0f-648b-91ba-1edf6be9d870" id="_a9ca2a6f-dc0f-648b-91ba-1edf6be9d870"></a>Natural Resources Canada
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo4;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast"><a name="_859221c7-976c-c863-f905-e9b771534dac" id="_859221c7-976c-c863-f905-e9b771534dac"></a>University of Calgary
</p>
</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <a name="_774a9e08-1903-6f5f-67b8-a92ca70d2368" id="_774a9e08-1903-6f5f-67b8-a92ca70d2368"></a>
        <h1>7.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Conventions</h1>
        <div><a name="_51f05389-393a-a51e-d999-e044930b17c6" id="_51f05389-393a-a51e-d999-e044930b17c6"></a><h2>7.1.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Overview</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_127b8a92-9c19-def6-f9ab-c53ac359ef16" id="_127b8a92-9c19-def6-f9ab-c53ac359ef16"></a>This section provides details and examples for any conventions used in the document. Examples of conventions are symbols, abbreviations, use of XML schema, or special notes regarding how to read the document.</p>
</div>
        <div><a name="_0f316dc5-0d09-171b-af59-87972ef36520" id="_0f316dc5-0d09-171b-af59-87972ef36520"></a><h2>7.2.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Identifiers</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_efdc70b6-5ba8-91e7-09c2-c17a1e52193e" id="_efdc70b6-5ba8-91e7-09c2-c17a1e52193e"></a>The normative provisions in this Standard are denoted by the URI</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_185cab25-e258-6baf-0c05-165ced699ae4" id="_185cab25-e258-6baf-0c05-165ced699ae4"></a><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0</a></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_24d5b731-bb6e-4c58-bab0-97fe98b19191" id="_24d5b731-bb6e-4c58-bab0-97fe98b19191"></a>All requirements and conformance tests that appear in this document are denoted by partial URIs which are relative to this base.</p>
</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <a name="_8aaabb61-f5de-acfb-66ce-a25dd7996e2d" id="_8aaabb61-f5de-acfb-66ce-a25dd7996e2d"></a>
        <h1>8.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Background and Motivation</h1>
        <div><a name="_3d25ca6e-237a-0351-4e1f-0159a83c38fd" id="_3d25ca6e-237a-0351-4e1f-0159a83c38fd"></a><h2>8.1.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Overview</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_bd89ab31-7f92-4645-8a93-4552f9c724ec" id="_bd89ab31-7f92-4645-8a93-4552f9c724ec"></a>Emissions measurement, monitoring, reporting, and verification (MMRV) now spans satellite remote sensing, aerial surveys, continuous in-situ monitoring, and handheld inspection instruments. Each modality generates data at different spatial and temporal scales, yet regulators, operators, and verifiers must reconcile these heterogeneous observations into coherent, auditable emission assessments. The absence of a common ontology and data model for emission events is the primary structural barrier to achieving this reconciliation at scale.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_aba5b239-9de5-09de-da5d-a72a9367337e" id="_aba5b239-9de5-09de-da5d-a72a9367337e"></a>EmissionML addresses this gap. It defines a standards-grounded conceptual model that provides a consistent semantic foundation for describing emission sources, events, quantities, and supporting observations &#x2014; independent of the sensing technology, reporting framework, or enterprise system that produces or consumes the data.</p>
</div>
        <div><a name="_3192d723-4b3c-9c10-151a-024756a27c96" id="_3192d723-4b3c-9c10-151a-024756a27c96"></a><h2>8.2.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Structural Gaps in Current Approaches</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_16c05643-2a06-f306-c817-50f128ed7722" id="_16c05643-2a06-f306-c817-50f128ed7722"></a>The emissions data ecosystem lacks a shared ontology. Each technology vendor, facility operator, and reporting program defines its own vocabulary, formats, and assumptions. This fragmentation produces systemic inefficiencies across the entire data lifecycle:</p>

<div class="ul_wrap"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo5;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_527eec0d-7cd2-282f-57bb-7ac997ce778c" id="_527eec0d-7cd2-282f-57bb-7ac997ce778c"></a><b>Costly, manual, and siloed workflows.</b> Operators must build bespoke integrations to reconcile proprietary vendor outputs with internal enterprise systems, duplicating effort for each new sensor or data source.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo5;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_c0b2d11e-134c-f484-0d0e-2991a4be5dd6" id="_c0b2d11e-134c-f484-0d0e-2991a4be5dd6"></a><b>Inability to link heterogeneous measurements.</b> A satellite-detected concentration anomaly and a ground-level inspection of the same source cannot be programmatically correlated when source features, event semantics, and observation metadata are defined inconsistently.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo5;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_20d08808-4ac7-44dd-d7d2-d26d613d500b" id="_20d08808-4ac7-44dd-d7d2-d26d613d500b"></a><b>Incompatible reporting requirements.</b> The same emission data must be restated in multiple incompatible templates to satisfy different regulatory and voluntary frameworks (e.g., EPA, EU Methane Regulation, OGMP 2.0, MiQ), increasing administrative burden and undermining cross-framework comparability.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo5;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast"><a name="_05229cce-5cd3-3c33-ea34-e0524ea3996a" id="_05229cce-5cd3-3c33-ea34-e0524ea3996a"></a><b>Lack of transparency and auditability.</b> Without a standard evidence chain linking reported quantities to their supporting observations and determination procedures, stakeholders cannot independently verify the credibility of emission assessments.
</p>
</div>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_b7256cc2-6973-5211-6ba8-ac5bdc8d6da8" id="_b7256cc2-6973-5211-6ba8-ac5bdc8d6da8"></a>These are not incidental inefficiencies. They are consequences of a missing data foundation: no common model exists for the emission event itself &#x2014; the central entity that connects a source, a mechanism, a quantity, a time interval, and the observations that support the determination.</p>
</div>
        <div><a name="_708a1d07-7bc7-9bcb-ec6e-7b09a6b92a2b" id="_708a1d07-7bc7-9bcb-ec6e-7b09a6b92a2b"></a><h2>8.3.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>How EmissionML Addresses These Gaps</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_396e9169-cdc2-1e4d-5c21-badce75515e2" id="_396e9169-cdc2-1e4d-5c21-badce75515e2"></a>EmissionML operationalizes open standards to provide a sensor-agnostic, interoperable data model for emission events. It establishes:</p>

<div class="ul_wrap"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_25a09a9b-bea1-f165-117f-f83c12a3c1f5" id="_25a09a9b-bea1-f165-117f-f83c12a3c1f5"></a><b>A shared ontology for emission events and their constituent parts</b> &#x2014; Source, Mechanism, Emission Quantity, Temporal Bound, Emission Intent, and Determination Procedure &#x2014; each with well-defined semantics and relationships.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_fb8a5274-001c-5eee-e856-efd08a9781d2" id="_fb8a5274-001c-5eee-e856-efd08a9781d2"></a><b>An explicit evidence chain</b> linking every emission determination to its supporting Observations (ISO/OGC 19156:2023, OMS 3.0) and procedures, enabling end-to-end traceability from reported values to underlying measurements.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_3ef01f38-9c98-15bb-cfab-a3ce185efbbd" id="_3ef01f38-9c98-15bb-cfab-a3ce185efbbd"></a><b>Embedded uncertainty provenance</b> through data quality metadata attached to emission quantities and temporal bounds, so that the confidence and precision of each determination are recorded alongside the values themselves.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast"><a name="_59d428e2-bfea-ada0-c0d0-d17b76c60bca" id="_59d428e2-bfea-ada0-c0d0-d17b76c60bca"></a><b>A &#x201C;write once, use many times&#x201D; intermediary model</b> that decouples data production from reporting consumption, enabling a single standards-conformant emission event record to be transformed into outputs for multiple regulatory and voluntary frameworks.
</p>
</div>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_134099c3-f449-d5b2-2fd9-dfe75e4c6787" id="_134099c3-f449-d5b2-2fd9-dfe75e4c6787"></a><a href="#fig-data-value-chain">Figure 1</a> illustrates this architecture. Heterogeneous inputs &#x2014; emission inventories, sensor observations, operational data, geospatial data, and field inspection and repair data &#x2014; are normalized through EmissionML into a single standards-conformant representation. From that representation, outputs are generated for multiple downstream consumers without requiring source-specific reformatting.</p>

<div class="figure"><a name="fig-data-value-chain" id="fig-data-value-chain"></a>

<p class="figure" style="page-break-after:avoid;"><img src="cid:3de662ef-0d44-4832-b7a4-f8cac1d7b701.png" height="323" width="489"/></p><p class="FigureTitle" style="text-align:center;">Figure 1&#xA0;&#x2014; EmissionML as an intermediary data model: write once, use many times</p></div>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_87b12f94-bd57-4c85-373f-24ce523af63b" id="_87b12f94-bd57-4c85-373f-24ce523af63b"></a>EmissionML does not replace existing sensing technologies, estimation methods, or reporting tools. It provides the standards-grounded data foundation that enables them to interoperate.</p>
</div>
        <div><a name="_cfcade47-58e7-cb20-e835-f8625e60b6ce" id="_cfcade47-58e7-cb20-e835-f8625e60b6ce"></a><h2>8.4.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Applicability Across Emission Domains</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_87ef3cbf-daa6-185d-e8b0-941d0687c148" id="_87ef3cbf-daa6-185d-e8b0-941d0687c148"></a>Although early development of EmissionML has been informed by oil and gas methane monitoring &#x2014; where regulatory pressure and sensing technology are most advanced &#x2014; the conceptual model is domain-neutral. The core abstraction of an emission event (a source releasing a substance through a mechanism, over a time interval, with a determined quantity) applies wherever substances are released into the atmosphere. Examples include:</p>

<div class="ul_wrap"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_73681b32-32ae-4e5d-676c-d564ff26c005" id="_73681b32-32ae-4e5d-676c-d564ff26c005"></a><b>Emergency management.</b> Wildfires, industrial accidents, and volcanic events produce large, episodic emissions whose source geometry, temporal bounds, and quantities must be characterized rapidly from heterogeneous observations (satellite imagery, ground sensors, dispersion models) and communicated across jurisdictions.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_9962db0f-2af3-bea1-6ca1-7fe65eaa99c3" id="_9962db0f-2af3-bea1-6ca1-7fe65eaa99c3"></a><b>Landfill gas emissions.</b> Landfills emit methane and other gases through diffuse and point sources that vary with waste composition, cover integrity, and weather conditions. Standardized emission event records enable consistent monitoring and reporting across sites and regulatory regimes.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_5adcd58d-4897-4dcc-8426-722563973f1f" id="_5adcd58d-4897-4dcc-8426-722563973f1f"></a><b>Permafrost thaw.</b> Thawing permafrost releases methane and carbon dioxide through mechanisms that are spatially diffuse and temporally variable. Reconciling field measurements, remote sensing, and biogeochemical models requires a common event model with explicit uncertainty provenance.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_2ae57f3d-1677-38fe-c055-730489ad88f3" id="_2ae57f3d-1677-38fe-c055-730489ad88f3"></a><b>Agriculture.</b> Livestock, rice cultivation, and fertilizer application produce emissions through distinct mechanisms at varying spatial scales. A shared ontology enables aggregation from field-level observations to regional inventories.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><a name="_01c9d3b3-1ead-179d-411d-fabd3355b032" id="_01c9d3b3-1ead-179d-411d-fabd3355b032"></a><b>Wastewater treatment.</b> Treatment processes emit methane, nitrous oxide, and other gases through identifiable mechanisms at known facilities, requiring the same source&#x2013;event&#x2013;observation linkage that EmissionML provides.
</p>
<p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7;" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast"><a name="_138c17e7-c05a-820d-96a4-cd0a8fb12386" id="_138c17e7-c05a-820d-96a4-cd0a8fb12386"></a><b>Public safety and hazardous releases.</b> Chemical spills, industrial gas leaks, and radiological dispersal events (e.g., dirty bombs) require rapid characterization of what substance was released, from where, in what quantity, and over what time interval &#x2014; the same source&#x2013;mechanism&#x2013;quantity&#x2013;temporal structure that EmissionML defines. A standardized event model enables interoperable data exchange across first responders, environmental agencies, and public health authorities.
</p>
</div>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_7fbdc03b-f2b9-d8c2-d107-d7e5e1258364" id="_7fbdc03b-f2b9-d8c2-d107-d7e5e1258364"></a>The EmissionML conceptual model accommodates these domains without modification to the core classes or relationships. Domain-specific extensions &#x2014; such as specialized Source Type or Mechanism vocabularies &#x2014; can be defined as profiles of the core model.</p>
</div>
        <div><a name="_89153faa-9531-d124-6e27-f3e143c8985c" id="_89153faa-9531-d124-6e27-f3e143c8985c"></a><h2>8.5.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Use Cases</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_3e82c43d-c8b5-0cc7-3a4f-c9f188df9ad2" id="_3e82c43d-c8b5-0cc7-3a4f-c9f188df9ad2"></a><a href="#tab-use-cases">Table 1</a> summarizes the key use cases that motivate the design of EmissionML.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 1&#xA0;&#x2014; EmissionML use cases</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;"><a name="tab-use-cases" id="tab-use-cases"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="37.5%"/><col width="37.5%"/></colgroup><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="25.0%">Use Case</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Problem</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">EmissionML Solution</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="25.0%">Cross-vendor sensor integration</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Proprietary payloads and inconsistent data models require bespoke integrations for each sensor system, increasing cost and preventing plug-and-play deployment.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Normalizes observation payloads to a consistent ontology, eliminating vendor-specific integration overhead.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="25.0%">Emission event attribution and validation</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Satellite-detected concentration anomalies cannot be programmatically linked to specific sources (e.g., facilities, landfill cells, wildfire perimeters) when source feature definitions are inconsistent across systems.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Links Observations to Source Features and Emission Events with an auditable validation chain, reducing attribution uncertainty.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="25.0%">Regulatory and voluntary reporting</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Operators reformat the same emission data for each reporting framework (EPA, EU Methane Regulation, OGMP 2.0, MiQ), duplicating effort and introducing transcription errors.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Provides a single standards-conformant emission event record that can be automatically transformed into multiple reporting formats.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="25.0%">Real-time operational response</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Control rooms and emergency response centres receive fragmented event feeds from multiple systems, delaying root-cause diagnosis and coordinated action.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Delivers a normalized, brokerable event stream with consistent source and quantity semantics across platforms.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="25.0%">Carbon-market quantification and verification</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Emission reduction calculations are opaque, with no standard mechanism to encode uncertainties or link quantities to their determination procedures.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Encodes emission quantities with uncertainties and provenance metadata, increasing credit integrity and reducing verification cost.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="25.0%">Emissions simulation interoperability</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Simulation tools use incompatible models, limiting cross-study comparability and reuse of inputs and outputs.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;" width="37.5%">Represents simulation inputs and outputs as standardized Emission Events, enabling benchmarking and reproducibility.</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Financial risk and ESG analysis</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="37.5%">ESG risk assessments depend on inconsistent, non-comparable emissions disclosures that cannot be reliably ingested into financial risk models.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="37.5%">Structures emissions data with standardized semantics and uncertainty metadata for direct ingestion into risk and ESG scoring models.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
</div>
        <div><a name="_b93b3d94-a76c-b347-b9fc-cd2af6e9bd53" id="_b93b3d94-a76c-b347-b9fc-cd2af6e9bd53"></a><h2>8.6.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Further Reading</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_478ad927-a0c4-8885-4388-c25730d4daae" id="_478ad927-a0c4-8885-4388-c25730d4daae"></a>The rationale, use cases, and design principles summarized in this clause are discussed in detail in the OGC EmissionML Discussion Paper <a href="#OGC_EmissionML_DP">OGC&#xA0;25-023</a>.</p>
</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <a name="_182d2647-0479-1702-2244-2330a8976856" id="_182d2647-0479-1702-2244-2330a8976856"></a>
        <h1>9.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Emission Event Data Model</h1>
        <div><a name="_4a583427-dc86-8d2f-4e90-52940b8ea431" id="_4a583427-dc86-8d2f-4e90-52940b8ea431"></a><h2>9.1.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Overview</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_f394abe7-5491-c6d8-408b-eec3116f5ae7" id="_f394abe7-5491-c6d8-408b-eec3116f5ae7"></a>The EmissionML conceptual model is described as a class diagram in <a href="#fig-emissionml-class-diagram">Figure 2</a>. The schema is fully described in x.x.x.</p>

<div class="figure"><a name="fig-emissionml-class-diagram" id="fig-emissionml-class-diagram"></a>

<p class="figure" style="page-break-after:avoid;"><img src="cid:ec737d53-8b6b-46ce-8fe9-aceb5417261f.png" height="120" width="489"/></p><p class="FigureTitle" style="text-align:center;">Figure 2&#xA0;&#x2014; EmissionML Abstract Conceptual Model</p></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 2&#xA0;&#x2014; UML relationship notation used in this standard</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;"><a name="_e5ae6ef5-7b54-bdcd-7ef4-f5d72c408d7a" id="_e5ae6ef5-7b54-bdcd-7ef4-f5d72c408d7a"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Symbol</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Name</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><img src="cid:da76d481-0c7b-4715-a180-8d4aee471612.png" height="186" alt="Composition" width="60"/></td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Composition</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The target is owned by and cannot exist without the source (e.g., EmissionEvent owns its EmissionQuantity and TemporalBound instances)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;"><img src="cid:69ab26d9-4f68-4e57-94b8-450089468a64.png" height="186" alt="Association" width="60"/></td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">Association</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">A directional reference between independent classes (e.g., EmissionEvent refers to a Source)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_1f52e683-a0ce-a038-b59c-1c5741a3a11e" id="_1f52e683-a0ce-a038-b59c-1c5741a3a11e"></a>Use the following table for Requirements Classes.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 3&#xA0;&#x2014; Requirements class &#x2014; Emission Event Conceptual Data Model Core</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_756bff0d-1962-c268-249f-a7591c89a9fc" id="_756bff0d-1962-c268-249f-a7591c89a9fc"></a><colgroup><col width="20%"/><col width="80%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="100.0%"><b>Emission Event Conceptual Data Model Core</b> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="100.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core</a> </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%">Target type</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%">Data Model</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%">Dependency</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/doc/as/om/3.0/req/obs-basic">http://www.opengis.net/doc/as/om/3.0/req/obs-basic</a></td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 1</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/emission-event">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/emission-event</a><br/> This requirement defines the Emission Event. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 2</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/source">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/source</a><br/> This requirement defines the Source. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 3</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/source-type">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/source-type</a><br/> This requirement defines the Source Type. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 4</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/mechanism">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/mechanism</a><br/> This requirement defines the Mechanism. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 5</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/emission-quantity">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/emission-quantity</a><br/> This requirement defines the Emission Quantity. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 6</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/unit-of-measure">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/unit-of-measure</a><br/> This requirement defines the Unit of Measure. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 7</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/temporal-bound">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/temporal-bound</a><br/> This requirement defines the Temporal Bound. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 8</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/observation">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/observation</a><br/> This requirement defines the Observation. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 9</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/emission-intent">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/emission-intent</a><br/> This requirement defines the Emission Intent. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 10</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/determination-procedure">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/determination-procedure</a><br/> This requirement defines the Determination Procedure. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 11</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/feature">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/feature</a><br/> This requirement defines the Feature. </td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="20.0%"><b>Requirement 12</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="80.0%"><a href="http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/procedure">http://www.opengis.net/spec/emissionml/1.0/req/datamodel/core/procedure</a><br/> This requirement defines the Procedure. </td></tr></tbody></table></div>
</div>
        <div><a name="_a21d2efe-86c2-0542-89ad-8a5642cb2a92" id="_a21d2efe-86c2-0542-89ad-8a5642cb2a92"></a><h2>9.2.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Emission Event Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_894b6be0-b127-6a5a-547d-d521cd14a12a" id="_894b6be0-b127-6a5a-547d-d521cd14a12a"></a>An Emission Event represents the release of a substance into the atmosphere over a non-zero duration. It is characterized by its start time and end time, the Source Feature from which the substance originated, and the identity and quantity of the emitted substance.</p><div class="Note"><a name="_f4e91f40-2795-b2f4-9c53-f51a777a4643" id="_f4e91f40-2795-b2f4-9c53-f51a777a4643"></a><p class="Note"><span class="note_label">NOTE 1:<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span></span>Conceptually, an Emission Event corresponds to an occurrent in upper-ontology terms, as it unfolds over time and has temporal parts.</p></div><div class="Note"><a name="_2e17c850-96e5-5e1f-8c4e-92f156abbe1e" id="_2e17c850-96e5-5e1f-8c4e-92f156abbe1e"></a><p class="Note"><span class="note_label">NOTE 2:<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span></span>For reporting or accounting purposes, a long-running emission event is often segmented into multiple time-bounded emission events (e.g., annual records). This segmentation reflects reporting conventions and does not imply physical cessation or re-initiation of the emission.</p></div>





<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 4&#xA0;&#x2014; Requirement 1 &#x2014; Emission Event Class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_7073cd42-eea5-d0fb-4d23-14b4bffdc26c" id="_7073cd42-eea5-d0fb-4d23-14b4bffdc26c"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%"><b>Requirement 1: Emission Event Class</b> </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/emission-event<br/> <br/> Each Emission Event class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#emission-event-attributes">Table 5</a>. Each Emission Event class shall have the direct relation between an Emission Event class and other classes listed in  <a href="#emission-event-relations">Table 6</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 5&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of an Emission Event class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="emission-event-attributes" id="emission-event-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">pollutantType</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The URI linking to an external definition of the pollutantType of the Emission Event.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">URI</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 6&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between an Emission Event class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="emission-event-relations" id="emission-event-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasMechanism</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The mechanism by which the emission occurred.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Mechanism</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasSource</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The source from which the emission originated.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Source</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">startTime</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The start time of the emission event.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">TemporalBound</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">endTime</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The end time of the emission event.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">TemporalBound</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">0..1 (optional)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasQuantity</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The quantity of the substance emitted.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">EmissionQuantity</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasStartTimeBasis</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The procedure used to determine the start time.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">DeterminationProcedure</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasEndTimeBasis</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The procedure used to determine the end time.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">DeterminationProcedure</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">0..1 (optional)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasQuantityBasis</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">The procedure used to determine the emission quantity.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">DeterminationProcedure</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasStartTimeEvidence</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Observations providing evidence for the start time determination.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Observation</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">0..* (optional)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">hasEndTimeEvidence</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Observations providing evidence for the end time determination.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Observation</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.0pt;page-break-after:avoid;">0..* (optional)</td></tr><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">hasQuantityEvidence</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">Observations providing evidence for the quantity determination.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">Observation</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">0..* (optional)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
</div>
        <div><a name="_b214d8a7-b79d-2eba-dac0-965952083eb4" id="_b214d8a7-b79d-2eba-dac0-965952083eb4"></a><h2>9.3.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Feature Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_112e425f-bb6f-e879-7227-8f50f8456a5f" id="_112e425f-bb6f-e879-7227-8f50f8456a5f"></a>A Feature is an abstraction of real world phenomena (Source: ISO 19101-1:2014). In EmissionML, Feature serves as the base class for entities that can be the ultimate feature of interest of an Observation. A Feature&#x2019;s <tt>geometry</tt> attribute provides the geospatial reference for the phenomenon it represents.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 7&#xA0;&#x2014; Requirement 11 &#x2014; Feature Class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_9fb006f9-53d4-8864-154a-defcf5a56013" id="_9fb006f9-53d4-8864-154a-defcf5a56013"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 11: Feature Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/feature<br/> + Each Feature class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#feature-attributes">Table 8</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 8&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of a Feature class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="feature-attributes" id="feature-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">geometry</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The spatial geometry of the feature.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">GM_Object</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">1 (mandatory)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 9&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between a Feature class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="feature-relations" id="feature-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">No direct relations are defined for Feature in the core model (it is referenced by Source via inheritance and by Observation via ultimateFeatureOfInterest).</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">-</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<hr/></div>
        <div><a name="_d3edd605-46b4-5a0c-f01d-91c242de5b07" id="_d3edd605-46b4-5a0c-f01d-91c242de5b07"></a><h2>9.4.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Source Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_7d2d6448-9117-08e4-d9b3-49e7f030f90f" id="_7d2d6448-9117-08e4-d9b3-49e7f030f90f"></a>A Source represents the feature from which an emission originates. A Source is an ISO 191xx feature whose geometry provides the geospatial reference for one or more Emission Events. A Source is characterised by its own identity, geometry, intended function, and lifecycle, and is explicitly agnostic to the Mechanism by which any associated Emission Event occurs.</p><div class="Note"><a name="_5ce66087-d6f5-afcc-7eb8-a977aa4233c4" id="_5ce66087-d6f5-afcc-7eb8-a977aa4233c4"></a><p class="Note"><span class="note_label">NOTE:<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span></span>A Source is a continuant that may exist independently of any emission, whereas an Emission Event is an occurrent. The identity and lifecycle of a Source are independent of the existence, absence, or frequency of Emission Events.</p></div>



<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 10&#xA0;&#x2014; Requirement 2 &#x2014; Source Class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_b0227602-1ec9-7bb3-bd4c-67b9b7c3d649" id="_b0227602-1ec9-7bb3-bd4c-67b9b7c3d649"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 2: Source Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/source<br/> + Each Source class shall inherit from Feature. Each Source class shall have the optional attributes listed in  <a href="#source-attributes">Table 11</a>. Each Source class shall have the direct relation between a Source class and other classes listed in  <a href="#source-relations">Table 12</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 11&#xA0;&#x2014; Attributes of a Source class (own attributes; geometry is inherited from Feature)</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="source-attributes" id="source-attributes"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Names</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Definition</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Data types and values</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">name</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">A human-readable name for the source.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">CharacterString</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">0..1 (optional)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 12&#xA0;&#x2014; Direct relation between a Source class and other class types</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="source-relations" id="source-relations"></a><thead><tr><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Role</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Description</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Target Class Type</th><th valign="middle" align="left" style="font-weight:bold;border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:avoid;">Multiplicity and use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">hasType</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">The type classification of the source.</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">SourceType</td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;">0..1 (optional)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

