        <div><a name="_495fc723-9cb0-5184-5e9b-13f511ae4435" id="_495fc723-9cb0-5184-5e9b-13f511ae4435"></a><h2>9.6.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Mechanism Class</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_2eb7baa4-4ec9-7021-471b-82441dcacf54" id="_2eb7baa4-4ec9-7021-471b-82441dcacf54"></a>A Mechanism is a classification of the specific physical, chemical, or operational process that constitutes the direct cause or pathway for an emission. It is defined independently of the Source&#x2014;including its identity, structure, or purpose&#x2014;allowing Mechanisms to be consistently reused across different types of Source.</p>

<p class="TableTitle" style="text-align:center;">Table 16&#xA0;&#x2014; Requirement 4 &#x2014; Mechanism Class</p><div align="center" class="table_container"><table class="MsoISOTable" style="mso-table-anchor-horizontal:column;mso-table-overlap:never;border-spacing:0;border-width:1px;" width="90%"><a name="_d2aa7191-468b-3e32-7b79-ccf1fd0f4d75" id="_d2aa7191-468b-3e32-7b79-ccf1fd0f4d75"></a><colgroup><col width="25%"/><col width="75%"/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="25.0%">Requirement 4: Mechanism Class </td><td valign="middle" align="left" style="border-top:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.5pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext 1.5pt;page-break-after:auto;" width="75.0%">/req/datamodel/core/mechanism<br/> + Each Mechanism class shall have the mandatory attributes listed in  <a href="#mechanism-attributes">Table 17</a>. Each Mechanism class shall have the direct relation listed in  <a href="#mechanism-relations">Table 18</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

